 #
 # Nuclear reaction
 #
 projectile          p     ptype0       type of incident particle
 element            Te     Starget      symbol of target nucleus
 mass              124     Atarget      mass number of target nucleus
 #
 # Accelerator 
 #
 Ebeam              12.000 Ebeam        incident energy in MeV
 Eback               8.000 Eback        lower end of energy range in MeV
 Ibeam               1.000 Ibeam        beam current in mA
 #
 # Output 
 #
 radiounit             gbq radiounit    unit for radioactivity
 yieldunit (massunit)  g   yieldunit    unit for isotope yield
 ZAoutput              n   flagZAoutput output files per Z, A instead of El, A
 #
 # Target
 #
 Tirrad              1     Tirrad       d of irradiation time
 Area                1.000 Area         target area in cm^2
 Tcool               1     Tcool        d of cooling time
 rho                -1.000 rho_target   target density [g/cm^3] 
 targetmass         -1.000 targetmass   target mass 
 selfshield            n flagselfshield flag for self-shielding 
 #
 # Cross section and decay data
 #
 Zdepth             10     Zdepth       depth to which Z numbers are scanned for cross sections
 Adepth             20     Adepth       depth to which A numbers are scanned for cross sections
 decay               y     flagdecay    flag to include decay of nuclides (n only for diagnosis) 


